About Us



Myers Industries (NYSE: MYE) is an international manufacturer of polymer-based material handling products and a wholesale distributor of tire repair and retread products.  As a diversified manufacturing company, Myers Industries offers a broad range of products across multiple markets, including industrial, agriculture, food processing, healthcare, and consumer. 




















	About Myers Industries – A Plastics Manufacturer and Tire Repair Supply Distributor






























































HOME CAREERS CONTACT




Menu















Search for:












About Us


history










            About Myers Industries - A Plastics Manufacturer and Tire Repair Supply Distributor 




        





            Myers Industries, Inc. is a diversified, international plastics manufacturer of returnable packaging, storage and safety products and specialty molding.  The Company is also the largest wholesale tire repair supply distributor in the United States.
 
Myers Industries was started in 1933, by Meyer and Louis Myers, as a tire supply storefront in Akron, Ohio.  In 1946, the Company began manufacturing plastic and rubber products related to the tire industry for distribution.
 
In 1963, Myers Industries, Inc. was established and grew into a diversified plastics manufacturer and tire repair supply distributor.  Over the last 50 years, Myers Industries has expanded to become a leading polymer manufacturer of material handling containers and wholesale distributor of tire repair and retread products for both domestic and international markets.
 
With over 2,500 experienced, dedicated employees, Myers Industries is committed to providing superior products that last.  Trust Myers Industries to deliver the highest quality products from the most experienced team in the industry.
 
Myers Industries, Inc. is traded on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol MYE and focuses on two core segments:  Material Handling and Distribution.


R. David Banyard Named President and CEO



In December 2015 the Company appointed R. David Banyard, president and CEO.  Prior to joining Myers, Mr. Banyard held the position of Group President, Fluid Handling Technologies at Roper Technologies, where he led a diverse portfolio of industrial businesses serving a wide array of end markets.  Mr. Banyard is currently working with the Myers' businesses to develop an enterprise strategy that will be the foundation for the Company's future growth.






