Myers Industries is a manufacturer of plastic and rubber products for industrial automotive, agricultural, consumer, and commercial markets. The company is divided into four segments: North American Material Handling, Lawn and Garden, Automotive and Custom and Distribution. With a headquarters… MoreMyers Industries is a manufacturer of plastic and rubber products for industrial automotive, agricultural, consumer, and commercial markets. The company is divided into four segments: North American Material Handling, Lawn and Garden, Automotive and Custom and Distribution. With a headquarters in Akron, OH, Myers Industries operates 22 manufacturing facilities and 37 distributions in the U.S. and internationally.
• Maintains a 100000 disaster recovery contract with IBM Business Continuity and Resiliency Services.

2013 and Earlier:
Myers Industries is a manufacturer of plastic and rubber products for industrial automotive, agricultural, consumer, and commercial markets. The company is divided into four segments:… More• Maintains a 100000 disaster recovery contract with IBM Business Continuity and Resiliency Services.

2013 and Earlier:
Myers Industries is a manufacturer of plastic and rubber products for industrial automotive, agricultural, consumer, and commercial markets. The company is divided into four segments: North American Material Handling, Lawn and Garden, Automotive and Custom and Distribution. With a headquarters in Akron, OH, Myers Industries operates 22 manufacturing facilities and 37 distributions in the U.S. and internationally.

The IT department at Myers Industries is run by a small corporate IT Management team in Akron, OH, led by the Director of Corporate IT. The primary responsibility of the department is the support of the company's manufacturing systems and network infrastructure.

The applications group handles the implementation and maintenance of the company's manufacturing systems and corporate applications. A team of architects oversee the in-house development of the enterprise applications. 
The organization uses Sharepoint in the cross-functional management of projects across its locations and divisions. The infrastructure group directs the operations of the data center and network infrastructure. A team of Help Desk administrators support the internal IT users, as well as the facilitating communication between the Akron HQS and external branches.





